The paper discusses the construction of graph algorithms, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of linear algebraic operations suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The application of graph algorithms also involves computational geometry (cs.CG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
